column3: I needed to get more work done at home.

column5: Sounds like you feel guilty for not getting more chores done. It's easy to feel this way when there is so much to do around the house!

column3: Listening to a colleague complain.
column4: It's very nice of you to be there for your colleague. At the same time, it can be upsetting and frustrating for you too.
column5: That sounds difficult. I'm sorry you had to go through that.

column3: I couldn't stop crying because I'm tired of being locked down in our house because of covid
column4: Sorry that you're having a hard time during lockdown. You're no alone. Many people are having a hard time adjusting.
column5: Sounds like you're having a hard time adjusting to this covid situation. You're not alone. Many people feel the same way.

column5: It's hard to not be worried when a loved one is not doing well.

column3: Being short with my daughters because they were not ready to go when i had asked them to be ready.

column5: Caregiving can be challenging sometimes, especially when you already have a lot on your plate.
